source.name: BBG 2009 Freedom of Information Act Repot
source.description: The Broadcasting Board of Governors' annual Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) report includes detailed statistics on the number and disposition of FOIA requests, including response times, volume of requests, and personnel costs. This information is being presented in a machine-readable format that allows members of the public, including public interest organizations, scholars and the media, to track the Agency's performance. This set covers fiscal year 2009.
